From 3204896c72277bf68a6022d55aefa8d73daf9eea Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: "Hermes (Cowork local session)" <hermes@local>
Date: Sun, 19 Jul 2026 01:10:45 -0300
Subject: [PATCH 1/2] fix: enforce feature parity before prediction

- Add src/feature_gate.py: deterministic fail-loud feature parity gate.
  Classifies the 126 trained features by family (matches P0 audit
  grouping) and judges missing / non-finite / stale values. Zero
  tolerance: any defect blocks parity.
- Wire the gate into AssetEngine._run_prediction() (src/predictor_server.py):
  missing trained features are no longer replaced with 0.0. When parity
  fails, latest_signal is forced to UNAVAILABLE, model_long/model_short
  .predict() are never called, and the failure is logged with a
  per-family breakdown.
- Add /api/feature-parity/{symbol} diagnostic endpoint exposing expected/
  populated feature counts, missing/invalid/stale names, per-family
  status, and whether inference is currently blocked.
- Add tests/test_feature_gate.py: deterministic fixture tests plus a
  real-booster smoke test reproducing the exact H-13 condition
  (41/126 populated, 85 missing, correctly blocked).

No models retrained. No thresholds changed. No risk logic changed. No
live trading enabled. No credentials added. Feature wiring for the 85
zero-fill-prone families is explicitly deferred to a future
admin-approved packet; this packet is scoped to the fail-loud gate (P1).
